abstract: >-
  PyBurgers is a high-performance solver for the 1D Stochastic
  Burgers Equation that implements both Direct Numerical Simulation
  (DNS) and Large-Eddy Simulation (LES) capabilities. The solver
  uses Fourier collocation methods for spatial derivatives and
  second-order Adams-Bashforth time integration, following the
  procedures described in Basu (2009). It features four subgrid-scale
  turbulence models, FFTW-optimized FFT operations with intelligent
  wisdom caching, and fractional Brownian motion stochastic forcing.
